{"title":"Sea Otter Classic 2024: Neuhaus Metalworks – HBSL Titanium XC Race 29er Hardtail – John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/neuhaus-metalworks-hbsl-xc-racing-29er-hardtail/","date":1713434403000,"content":"<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://1up-usa.com/\" target=\"_blank\">1-Up USA</a> for sponsoring our Sea Otter Classic 2024 coverage!</strong></p>\n<p>Josh and John are out at Sea Otter this week, covering people, products, and bikes on display. We’re starting the show coverage off a little differently this year with a feature on Neuhaus Metalworks’ newest offering: the HBSL Titanium XC Race 29er. Read on for a look at this new titanium Superleggera chassis and a comparison to the steel Hummingbird hardtail 29er…<span></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p></p>\n<div></div>\n<p><em>Neuhaus Metalworks 120 mm Hummingbird Steel in peach powder coat and the Titanium HBSL 110 mm XC Race bike in blue cerakote…</em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-19.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-19.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-19.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-19.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-19.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>John here, reporting from Sea Otter, where yesterday I meandered the aisles during the showcase setup day, looking for familiar faces and getting a lay of the land. One of the folks I bumped into was Nick from Neuhaus Metalworks, who was swapping out a fork at the MRP booth on a beautiful peach-colored Hummingbird 29er.</p>\n<p><em>Daniel, the other half of Neuhaus, wasn’t on deck at the show today, but don’t worry, we’ve got something special planned with him!</em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-23.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-23.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-23.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-23.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-23.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>We’ve written extensively about Neuhaus and the <a href=\"https://www.neuhausmetalworks.com/store/p/hummingbird\" target=\"_blank\">Hummingbird</a>, so check out these articles for the 411 on the brand and its flagship 29er hardtail:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/neuhaus-metalworks-shop-visit/\" target=\"_blank\">Inside / Out at Neuhaus Metalworks and a Look at the Hummingbird Steel Hardtail 29er</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/neuhaus-metalworks-hummingbird-29er-hardtail-review/\" target=\"_blank\">The Current Hardtail Moment: Hailey Reviews the Neuhaus Metalworks Hummingbird 29er Hardtail</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-65.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-65.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-65.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-65.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-65.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<h3>The All-New Titanium HBSL 29er XC Race Hardtail</h3>\n<p>Today, I’m sharing the latest model from the brand: the HBSL or <em>Hummingbird Superleggera</em>. The intent of the HBSL is to offer a made-in-the-USA production stock-sized titanium XC racing hardtail with cerakote to match MRP’s color offerings, priced competitively at $3,000 for a frame.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-28.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-28.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-28.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-28.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-28.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>HBSL Quick Hits:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>$3000 MSPR frame</li>\n<li>Titanium (<a href=\"https://theradavist.com/moots-womble-review/\" target=\"_blank\">is immortal!</a>)</li>\n<li>US built from international components</li>\n<li>110 mm travel</li>\n<li>2.4″ tire clearance</li>\n<li>14 stock sizes</li>\n<li>Cerakote colors match the MRP custom program</li>\n<li>Size-dependent butting profiles for tubing</li>\n<li>67º head tube angle and 74º seat tube angle for M/L</li>\n<li>3.3 lb frame for size M/L</li>\n<li>As built size M/L – 22 lbs with <a href=\"https://gulocomposites.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Gulo carbon wheels</a> or 24 lbs with <a href=\"https://astralcycling.com/collections/serpentine-carbon-x/\" target=\"_blank\">Astral and White Industries wheels</a></li>\n<li>Fewer “customized” options to keep production costs down</li>\n<li>Non-sliding dropouts</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-61.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-61.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-61.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-61.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-61.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1334\" height=\"2000\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-30.jpg?fit=1200,2000&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-30.jpg?w=1334&amp;quality=75 1334w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-30.jpg?resize=1200,1799&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-30.jpg?resize=768,1151&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-30.jpg?resize=1025,1536&amp;quality=75 1025w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-46.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-46.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-46.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-46.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-46.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The original Hummingbird is specced with 80-130 mm travel (based on frame size) trail/all-rounder hardtail. <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/neuhaus-metalworks-hummingbird-29er-hardtail-review/\" target=\"_blank\">Hailey lauded its abilities in her review,</a> and I even <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/neuhaus-metalworks-hummingbird-29er-hardtail-review/\" target=\"_blank\">I felt it to be incredibly balanced</a> for a travel spec I don’t normally ride. The HBSL and its 110 mm travel is meant to be just a little bit faster and lighter than its Hummingbird 120 mm cousin.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?fit=1200,1333&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?resize=1024,682&amp;quality=75 1024w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?resize=1800,1200&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?resize=1335,890&amp;quality=75 1335w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?resize=700,467&amp;quality=75 700w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2023/05/Neuhaus-Hummingbird-29er-Review-16.jpg?resize=1536,1024&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>“You could run a 110 mm air-sprung, tuned MRP Ribbon SL or a Fox 34 Stepcast fork and hit the rowdy stuff, and then for ultralight racing, run a Fox 32 or RockShox Sid Race Day.” Explained Nick from Neuhaus as we wheeled HBSL to a photo shoot location.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-40.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-40.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-40.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-40.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-40.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-59.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-59.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-59.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-59.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-59.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>One place that Neuhaus didn’t skimp on weight was the 3D-printed components the brand is known for. This chainstay yoke isn’t as lightweight as a simple crimped and shaped chainstay, but it is crucial to the brand’s multiple-size offerings and faster production.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-47.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-47.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-47.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-47.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-47.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-38.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-38.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-38.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-38.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-38.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-57.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-57.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-57.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-57.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-57.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>The HBSL uses size-dependent, custom-drawn, and butted tubing <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/taichung-taiwan-is-a-bicycling-manufacturing-mecca/\" target=\"_blank\">sourced from Taiwan</a>, along with the 3D printed/sintered components made in Shanghai, China. It’s all welded together in batches in Marin County, California, the home to many mountain bike innovators.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"2000\" height=\"1334\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-66.jpg?fit=1200,1334&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-66.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75 2000w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-66.jpg?resize=1200,800&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-66.jpg?resize=768,512&amp;quality=75 768w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/04/Sea_Otter_Classic-2024_NeuhausMetalworks-66.jpg?resize=1536,1025&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>If you’re going to the Sea Otter Classic this year, be sure to swing through the <a href=\"https://mrpbike.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MRP</a> booth to see a <a href=\"https://www.neuhausmetalworks.com/store/p/hummingbird\" target=\"_blank\">steel Hummingbird</a> and the <a href=\"https://5dev.com/\" target=\"_blank\">5Dev</a> booth to see the all-new HBSL on display.</p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://www.neuhausmetalworks.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Neuhaus Metalworks</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/neuhaus-metalworks-hbsl-xc-racing-29er-hardtail/\">Sea Otter Classic 2024: Neuhaus Metalworks – HBSL Titanium XC Race 29er Hardtail</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"61978c2c5bb76dfc35e14de7ba2739e4df1b6bb2fed0f9973b2acaede77e5bf4","category":"Cycling"}